Interface Decompressor

    • Method Detail

      • decompress

        io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf decompress​(io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf input,
                                   io.netty.buffer.ByteBufAllocator allocator)
                            throws DecompressionException
        This method will read from the input ByteBuf and decompress into a new ByteBuf that will be allocated (if needed) from the ByteBufAllocator. If there is not enough readable data in the ByteBuf to process it will return null. This method should be called in a loop as long:
        • isFinished() is false
          something was read from the input
          something was returned
        • Otherwise this method should be called again once there is more data in the input buffer.
Parameters:
input - the ByteBuf that contains the data to be decompressed.
allocator - the ByteBufAllocator that is used to allocate a new buffer (if needed) to write the decompressed bytes too.
Returns:
the ByteBuf that contains the decompressed data. The caller of this method takes ownership of the buffer. The return value will be null if there is not enough data readable in the input to make any progress. In this case the user should call it again once there is more data ready to be consumed.
Throws:
DecompressionException - thrown if an decompression error was encountered or the decompressor was closed before.

  • isFinished

    boolean isFinished()
    Returns true if the decompressor was finish. This might be because the decompressor was explicitly closed or the end of the compressed stream was detected.
    Returns:
    true if the decompressor is done with decompressing the stream.

  • isClosed

    boolean isClosed()
    Return true if the decompressor was closed, false otherwise.
    Returns:
    if close() was called.

  • close

    void close()
    Close the decompressor. After this method was called isFinished() will return true as well and it is not allowed to call decompress(ByteBuf, ByteBufAllocator) anymore.
    Specified by:
    close in interface AutoCloseable
